The man who bragged on Facebook about defiling a class four pupil denied charges of promoting sexual offences on Tuesday.Calvin Alfayo alias Mohamed Alfayo was charged with committing the offences on October 3 at Chepilat trading center in Sotik division, Bomet county.Alfayo is said to have distributed photographs and articles which promoted or were intended to promote sexual offences with a child.He committed the offences contrary to section 12(a) and sexual offenses act No.3 of 2006.Sotik senior resident magistrate Bernard Omwansa released him on Sh100,000 bond with a surety of the same amount.The case will be mentioned on October 25 and heard on November 21.Read: Man who defiled class four pupil charged with 'promoting sexual offence with child'Also read: Man-as-hunter mindset destructive